summary:
The Security Council,
 Recalling previous resolutions and statements, 
 Recalling the Lusaka Ceasefire Agreement and the respected ceasefire since January 2001, 
 and the essential Inter-Congolese Dialogue for peace, 
Determining the situation in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) threatens international peace and security,

 Condemns the resumption of fighting in Moliro and its capture by RCD-Goma as a major ceasefire violation; 
Stresses no party should make military gains during the peace process and peacekeeping operation;

Demands RCD-Goma withdraw from Moliro and all parties to withdraw to defensive positions; 
Demands RCD-Goma withdraw from Pweto and other locations occupied in contravention of disengagement plans; 

Recalls Kisangani's demilitarization; 
Reminds parties to comply with ceasefire, disengagement plans, and Council resolutions; 

Calls on Rwanda to influence RCD-Goma to implement demands; 
Welcomes MONUC deployment and calls for cooperation and personnel safety; 

Urges parties to refrain from military action during the Inter-Congolese Dialogue; 
Stresses dialogue continuation and calls on the DRC Government to resume participation; 

Decides to remain seized of the matter.
